{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XqdLGKpJSMkHW5b2jbakHK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the ES Docker image comes with a pre-existing `elasticsearch.keystore` file in the config directory! This means the init container will also have a pre-created keystore (since it uses the same image). Great, so I don't need the `if [ ! -f ... ]; then elasticsearch-keystore create; fi` check.\n\nNow let me also check if the plugin install might require a specific user. The ES Docker container typically runs as uid 1000 (`elasticsearch`). The init container might run as root, which could cause permission issues.\nI need to look at the security context and trace through the entrypoint logic more carefully. Since security is disabled in the config, the keystore creation check might be skipped entirely, so I should verify what the entrypoint actually does in that scenario.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14675,"cache_read_input_tokens":46972,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":14675},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e4d26ef-e625-4852-b3b0-6670cb72b7c6","uuid":"1abda775-d056-4ee7-85f7-b3494fa3ab20","request_id":"req_011CcMvxbuTaX24yEh7C4EBu"}
