{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01H5rpQxDJdaFXbhU48VgJnS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Root causes fixed:**\n1. **Missing MinIO Service** — created `Service/minio` so `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000` resolves\n2. **Missing `es-backups` bucket** — created via a one-off `minio/mc` Job (the original `minio-init` job had failed because the Service didn't exist yet)\n3. **No `repository-s3` plugin** — not installed in the base ES 7.17.9 image\n\n**Configuration applied:**\n- Created `Secret/es-secure-settings` with `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` (credentials from `minio-root` secret: `minioadmin`)\n- Updated the `es-config` ConfigMap with `s3.client.default.endpoint`, `protocol: http`, and `path_style_access: true` (non-credential settings safe for elasticsearch.yml)\n- Patched the StatefulSet with two init containers:\n  - `install-s3-plugin`: downloads and installs the `repository-s3` plugin into a shared emptyDir, mounted into the main container at the plugin path\n  - `init-keystore`: reads credentials from `es-secure-settings` Secret and writes them into the ES keystore, mounted via `subPath` so credentials survive pod restarts without appearing in env vars or elasticsearch.yml\n\n**Result:** Snapshot `snapshot-1` in repository `minio-repo` completed with `state: SUCCESS`, 2 shards snapshotted, 0 failures."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":554,"cache_read_input_tokens":79241,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":554},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e4d26ef-e625-4852-b3b0-6670cb72b7c6","uuid":"bbdcb157-f103-4d80-a3a9-57e9793a7ce1","request_id":"req_011CcMwigMaBpXUZ9yQefyJA"}
